In England, in the seven days to 29 January, there were 605,032 new confirmed cases (1,069.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 January, there were 636,210 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 5% (31,178 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 03 February is 15,106,124 (26,712.8 cases per 100,000 population).
